^["stream"]{
 >>[2026-04-15 23:35] observe — the normalized settings model already supports global readouts, but declarative trigger controls are still effectively treated as scope-local behavior.
 >>[2026-04-15 23:38] observe — `/settings/` currently orders technical maps and registries too close to the top, which makes the page feel like inspection-first instead of experience-first.
 >>[2026-04-15 23:40] decide — center this pass on a reusable variant-widget pattern that can live on `/settings/` and on flagship routes without inventing a second control vocabulary.
 >>[2026-04-15 23:42] hygiene — base ref recorded as main@81d5e5205d70; unrelated local edits exist in play/shared-css files and will be avoided.
 >>[2026-04-15 23:43] taste — the widget copy should read like an invitation to shape the site, not like a hidden settings lab.
 >>[2026-04-15 23:45] revise — user feedback confirms the current settings page order feels off, so the plan now explicitly prioritizes route order and quick-start clarity before ornament.
 >>[2026-04-16 00:02] implement — added shared `vibe-widget` surface classes so the same mini-card grammar can live on `/settings/`, `/`, `/topics/software/`, and `/topics/math/`.
 >>[2026-04-16 00:07] implement — widened `public/js/site-settings.js` just enough to support standalone `data-site-setting-set` controls, active-state syncing, and local status feedback outside scoped settings forms.
 >>[2026-04-16 00:12] implement — rebuilt the top of `/settings/` into a quick-start surface with presets, current-vibe feedback, and immediate color/palette/memory variants, then reordered the deeper inspection sections below it via route CSS.
 >>[2026-04-16 00:16] implement — replaced the older one-purpose strips on home, software, and math with portable vibe widgets that expose current state plus a few tailored variants.
 >>[2026-04-16 00:18] verify — node --check passed for public/js/site-settings.js and git diff --check passed after the settings/widget rollout.
}

